UID:20260904-DeadlineforcharterproposalstoreachtheNov@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260720T105829Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260904
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260905
SUMMARY:Deadline for charter proposals to reach the November ballot
DESCRIPTION:Mamdani's Commission on Government Efficiency finished its 10
  public hearings and published a preliminary staff report on July 2. To 
 put charter amendments before voters on Nov. 3\, it must file them with 
 the city clerk at least 60 days beforehand. No filing date has been anno
 unced\; this is the outer bound the law implies\, not a scheduled event.
  The preliminary report points at outdoor dining\, permitting\, procurem
 ent\, bus and street infrastructure and a rainy day fund.\n\nhttps://www
 .nyc.gov/site/charter/reports/coge-reports.page
URL:https://www.nyc.gov/site/charter/reports/coge-reports.page
CATEGORIES:cityhall
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
